  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "description": "Encapsulation is the principle of bundling data and the operations that act on that data into a single unit (typically a [class](./class.md) or module) and restricting direct access to the internal state. By exposing only a defined interface, encapsulation protects invariants: the [object](./object.md)'s internal state can only change through methods that maintain consistency.",
